pulltitle: Fix v4 plugin counting
pullsbody:
This fixes [bug 1220110](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1220110) & [bug 1220119](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1220119).
- Plugins with multiple binaries were collapsed into one entry in the
  add-on manager (based on name & description), but counted as multiple
  in about:healthreport.
  I updated this to use the same collapsing strategy to avoid confusion.
- Before bug 1218842 / bug 1222503, GMP plugins were present in the
  environment even if disabled.
  They are now filtered out in about:healthreport to get correct counts.
pull_repo_desc: Content that will appear in about:healthreport
pull_commit_message:
Fix v4 plugin counting

This fixes bug 1220110 & bug 1220119:
https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1220110
https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1220119

* Plugins with multiple binaries were collapsed into one entry in the
add-on manager (based on name & description), but counted as multiple
in about:healthreport.
I updated this to use the same collapsing strategy to avoid confusion.
* Before bug 1218842 / bug 1222503, GMP plugins were present in the
environment even if disabled.
They are now filtered out in about:healthreport to get correct counts.

pulltitle: Update v4 content to run from v4 data
pullsbody:
This updates the remote content here to be powered by the v4 client data (see [bug 1150491](https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1150491) for more background).

Simple testing steps:
- checkout
- build from top source dir: `./generate.py --output-dir html -f`
- start server in top source dir: `python -m SimpleHTTPServer 8000`
- go to `about:config` and change `datareporting.healthreport.about.reportUrl` to `http://localhost:8000/html/%LOCALE%/v4/`
- visit `about:healthreport`

Note that the v4 unit test currently is not integrated in the grunt build due to complications (old PhantomJS instance vs newer JS & no proper error output).
You can run it manually for now by navigating to `http://localhost:8000/tests/unit_v4.html`.
We are ok with running it manually for now to avoid blocking this bug, medium-term we want to switch this over to more modern tests (probably Node.js based) that have better support within Mozilla.
pull_repo_desc: Content that will appear in about:healthreport
pull_commit_message: Add v4 files (just copies)

pulltitle: Copy files to v4 directory for unified telemetry
pullsbody:
The new unified telemetry will take the place of the old FHR mechanism for the "health report", including a change to the API. The data collected and reported for the health report (base data, opt-out data for the release population) remains essentially the same; the UX presented to the user remains essentially the same.

We'll have both older and newer clients out in the wild for some time, so we need to host two versions of this content, which make use of the two APIs. Our proposal is to create a 'v4' version of the site that mirrors the files at the root directory, with minor changes. URLs then become:
fhr v2:  https://fhr.cdn.mozilla.net/%LOCALE%/
mobile:  https://fhr.cdn.mozilla.net/%LOCALE%/mobile/
unified telemetry/fhr v4:  https://fhr.cdn.mozilla.net/%LOCALE%/v4/

This PR currently copies the various files into the static v4 directory, and then sets up symlinks in the various locale directories (following the same pattern as the v2/html files).

It does not yet copy a new index or js files. (@bsmedberg will make the API changes.) Pushing this as is would allow us to go ahead and patch the client with the new v4 url. https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1180673 

I've tested the v4 url by changing my browser settings, and loading various locales directly in the browser.

@lauraxt, @lonnen r? (let me know if I've missed anything or need to make changes for local tests)
/cc @georgf
pull_repo_desc: Content that will appear in about:healthreport
pull_commit_message: Copy files to v4 folder for unified telemetry

pullsbody:
@lauraxt r? There is no reliable way to get the user's actual chosen locale and, calling toLocaleDateString on the Date object without specifying any locales seems to have no effect (possibly for the same above reason).

Therefore I decided to use the locale stored in the FHR payload and failing that (or there being no support for the locale), just fallback to en-US.

pulltitle: Fix Bug 904592, enable l10n for FHR for Android
pullsbody:
@lauraxt r?

So, I do not know if my Python is as Pythonic as it can be and I need some feedback also from Pascal regarding the l10n hooks but, all in all, it works.

The generate script now takes a new parameter called --platform that can either be desktop or mobile. If you do not pass anything, it defaults to desktop. Also, if you do not specify a output-dir it will write to a build directory at the root of the repo as such:

```
/build
  /html
```

and

```
/build
  /mobile
```

respectively.

pulltitle: bump pytest_mozwebqa to v1.1 to gain support for --skipurlcheck
pullsbody: Bumping the version number of pytest-mozwebqa to 1.1 so we can gain the --skipurlcheck flag. This change only effects our Selenium tests; the default behavior of pytest-mozwebqa is to do a schema check of --baseurl. Ultimately because we're testing against about:healthreport we need this functionality. https://github.com/davehunt/pytest-mozwebqa/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#11

pulltitle: adding a debug mode in which you can render the FHR page with custom JSON
pullsbody:
@laura r? To use this, simple open up config.json inside the js folder, set debug to true. Next open up json/payload.json and paste in the custom payload you want to test. Then simply run generate and load up the FHR page as you normally would.

To switch debugging off, simply set debug to false and it will render with data from the FHR data service.

pullsbody:
Main changes:
- Created a new plot for startup times and health indicators (FHRPlot in fhr.js) with corresponding CSS styles. Some additional features not intended for the first version are left commented out.
- Updated data packaging method as getGraphData() in data.js.
- Created generate-basic.py to generate the en-US version of the page without worrying about localizaton (for testing purposes).
- Added reference to d3.v3.min.js in index.html (and added to js folder). 
- Updated yaxis label to be positioned relative to the graph rather than the outer graphbox.

Main changes:
- Created a new plot for startup times and health indicators (FHRPlot in fhr.js) with corresponding CSS styles. Some additional features not intended for the first version are left commented out.
- Updated data packaging method as getGraphData() in data.js.
- Created generate-basic.py to generate the en-US version of the page without worrying about localizaton (for testing purposes).
- Added reference to d3.v3.min.js in index.html (and added to js folder). 
- Updated yaxis label to be positioned relative to the graph rather than the outer graphbox.
pull_repo_desc: Content that will appear in about:healthreport
pull_commit_message:
Merge pull request #71 from ossreleasefeed/bug858242-fix-policy-links

fixes policy links for bug858242
